nstall Sass Globally (Command Line)
Ensure Node.js is Installed:
Check if Node.js is installed by running node -v in your terminal. If not, download and install it from nodejs.org.
Install Sass Globally:
Run the following command in your terminal to install Sass globally using npm:
bash

npm install -g sass
This allows you to use the sass command anywhere on your system.
Verify Installation:
Check if Sass is installed by running:
bash

sass --version
You should see the version number (e.g., 1.77.8 as of the latest release).
Use Sass in Your Project:
Navigate to your project directory.
Compile a Sass file to CSS. For example:
bash

sass input.scss output.css
To watch for changes and auto-compile:
bash

sass --watch input.scss:output.css
